<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Empress" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Empress</orth> (sometimes trisyll. in Tit.; f. i. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.240.11" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.240.11" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 240</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.2.143" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 143</bibl>), 1) the consort of an emperor: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 4, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.141" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.255" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 255</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 3, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.240" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 240</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.240" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 240</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.240" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 240</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.1.20" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.143" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 32</bibl> etc.<lb />2) a female sovereign: <cit><quote>the general of our gracious e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V Chor.</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V Chor.</bibl> <cit><quote>madam, O good e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.11.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 11, 33</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.15.71" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 15, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 71</bibl>.
<lb />3) sovereign mistress: <cit><quote>e. of my love,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 56</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>of my soul,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 40</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>